<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFC66A79F8269CC01676B048" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFC66A79F8269CC01676B048" blockId="61.[2009,2606,2515,2938]" pageId="61" pageNumber="819">
Originally described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC66A79F8269C991673B1EF" baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[2010,2163,2752,2781]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="somalica">N. somalica</taxonomicName>
; it is treated as a separate species based on cranial traits, and perhaps also bacular morphology. Its distinction from 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC66A79F7D09D6B16BFB061" authorityName="Thomas &amp; Schwann" authorityYear="1905" box="[2092,2239,2866,2899]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="matroka">N. matroka</taxonomicName>
is still open to question. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFC66A79F8249DD819D7B0F5" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" type="distribution">
<caption id="90EB6676FFC66A79F8249DD819D7B0F5" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6398025" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6398025" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6398025/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" targetBox="[1393,1985,2525,2939]" targetPageId="61">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFC66A79F8249DD819D7B0F5" blockId="61.[1395,2602,2945,3213]" pageId="61" pageNumber="819">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFC66A79F8249DD81688B090" bold="true" box="[2008,2184,2945,2978]" pageId="61" pageNumber="819">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="BC83766EFFC66A79F7559DD8174DB090" box="[2217,2381,2945,2978]" name="Madagascar" pageId="61" pageNumber="819">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, known only from four localities around the Isalo Massif.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFC66A7AFA8F9D961AEEBA5F" lastPageId="62" lastPageNumber="820" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" type="description">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFC66A7AFA8F9D961AEEBA5F" blockId="61.[1395,2602,2945,3213]" lastBlockId="62.[167,1374,292,881]" lastPageId="62" lastPageNumber="820" pageId="61" pageNumber="819">
<emphasis id="F6E0EAECFFC66A79FA8F9D96186CB0C2" bold="true" box="[1395,1644,3023,3056]" pageId="61" pageNumber="819">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Tail 30-4 mm, ear 9-8 mm, hindfoot 5: 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFFC66A79F76A9D9616E9B0C2" box="[2198,2281,3023,3056]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
(one specimen), forearm 30-1-32 mm. Dorsal pelage of the Isalo Serotine is dark brown, with mid-dorsal hairs c¢. 
<quantity id="036C9B1BFFC66A79FA259A471826B70D" box="[1497,1574,3102,3135]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" unit="mm" value="7.0">7 mm</quantity>
long; ventral pelage is sharply bicolored, with a mixture of dark buff and gray, becoming paler toward tail. Ears are mid-brown and translucent. Single available baculum is 2-2 mm long, has distal end flattened and deflected ventrally, as in the Malagasy Serotine (
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC56A7AFE41977D1C54BA77" authorityName="Thomas &amp; Schwann" authorityYear="1905" box="[445,596,292,325]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="62" pageNumber="820" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="matroka">N. matroka</taxonomicName>
), but has a smaller surface area, and lateral flanges and vertical projection are less developed; dental morphology of the two is similar.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="90EB6676FFC66A79FF8B9ABD172EB691" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6398519" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6398519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6398519/files/figure.png" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" startId="61.[119,149,3300,3325]" targetBox="[12,2753,18,3658]" targetPageId="60">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFC66A79FF8B9ABD172EB691" blockId="61.[116,2601,3282,3495]" pageId="61" pageNumber="819">
On following pages: 121. Roberts's Serotine (
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC66A79FD999ABF1D3DB7CD" box="[613,829,3302,3327]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="robertsi">Neoromicia robertsi</taxonomicName>
); 122. Stanley's Serotine (
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC66A79FBA19AB11AD9B633" box="[1117,1241,3304,3329]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Neoromicia</taxonomicName>
stanleyi); 123. Zulu Serotine (
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC66A79F9DD9AB3190CB631" baseAuthorityName="Roberts" baseAuthorityYear="1924" box="[1569,1804,3306,3331]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="zuluensis">Neoromicia zuluensis</taxonomicName>
): 124. Tiny Serotine (
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC66A79F80A9AB516F1B637" baseAuthorityName="Bocage" baseAuthorityYear="1889" box="[2038,2289,3308,3333]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="guineensis">Neoromicia guineensis</taxonomicName>
); 125. 
<collectingRegion id="0650F81CFFC66A79F6C19AB41785B634" box="[2365,2437,3309,3334]" country="Ethiopia" name="Sumale" pageId="61" pageNumber="819">Somali</collectingRegion>
Serotine (
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC66A79FF829B561F63B617" baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1901" box="[126,355,3343,3365]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="somalica">Neoromicia somalica</taxonomicName>
); 126. Banana Serotine (
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC66A79FD8D9B481D36B615" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[625,822,3345,3367]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nanus">Neoromicia nanus</taxonomicName>
); 127. Rendall’'s Serotine (
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC66A79FBAD9B4A1ACDB61A" box="[1105,1229,3347,3368]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Neoromicia</taxonomicName>
rendall): 128. Dark-brown Serotine (
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC66A79F99D9B4C193EB619" baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[1633,1854,3349,3371]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brunnea">Neoromicia brunnea</taxonomicName>
); 129. Rosevear's Serotine (
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC66A79F78F9B4E16EFB61E" box="[2163,2287,3351,3372]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Neoromicia</taxonomicName>
rosevear): 130. Isabelline Serotine (
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC66A79FF1D9B6E1F5DB67E" box="[225,349,3383,3404]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Neoromicia</taxonomicName>
isabella); 131. Grandidier’s Serotine (
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC66A79FD0F9B631DEBB67D" authorityName="Dobson" authorityYear="1876" box="[755,1003,3386,3407]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="823" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="grandidieri">Neoromicia grandidieri</taxonomicName>
); 132. White-winged Serotine (
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFC66A79FABE9B65183EB660" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[1346,1598,3388,3410]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Neoromicia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="61" pageNumber="819" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tenuipinnis">Neoromicia tenuipinnis</taxonomicName>
); 133. Heller's Serotine (
